 g(t)=F(tx) \qquad \forall t\in\mathbb{R}. 
 g'(t)=dF_{tx}(x). 
 g'(t)=Ax\qquad \forall t\in\mathbb{R}. 
 F(x)-F(0)=g(1)-g(0)=\int_0^1g'(t)dt=\int_0^1Axdt=Ax. 
